{"title":"Radsporttechnik Müller builds a properly wide, insanely light 1060g 29″ Boost XC wheelset","link":"https://bikerumor.com/radsporttechnik-muller-builds-a-properly-wide-insanely-light-1060g-29-boost-xc-wheelset/","date":1638212577000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2.png\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"538\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-800x538.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-800x538.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-297x200.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-120x81.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-768x517.png 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130924/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2.png 933w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-279464\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>There’s light, and then there’s <em>light</em><em>. </em>Or Extralite, as it may be. That’s certainly on order with one of the lightest 29″ XC wheelsets with a wide internal rim width that we’ve seen. Of course, they also include a heavy price tag and a light rider weight limit, but if weight savings is the main goal, these wheels will be hard to beat.</p><div id=\"attachment_279469\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-279469\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.jpg\" alt=\"Radsporttechnik Mueller 29 MXCR Carbon Boost Extralite Hyper 3 Sapim CX Super wheelset\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.jpg 1440w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-240x300.jpg 240w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-96x120.jpg 96w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-768x960.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130926/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-1229x1536.jpg 1229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-279469\">All photos c. Radsporttechnik Mueller</p></div><p>Built by Radsporttechnik Müller in Germany, these are just one of many wheel builds offered by the light weight specialist. This build starts with the MXC Carbon 29″ rim which features a properly wide, 30mm internal width. The rims are 28h, and weigh just&nbsp;<em>285g</em> each.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4.png\" alt=\"Extralite Hyperboost 3 front hub\" width=\"964\" height=\"625\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4.png 964w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4-297x193.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4-800x519.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4-120x78.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130937/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-4-768x498.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 964px) 100vw, 964px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.png\" alt=\"Extralite Hyperboost 3 rear hub\" width=\"974\" height=\"646\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3.png 974w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-297x197.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-800x531.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-120x80.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130930/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-3-768x509.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 974px) 100vw, 974px\"></a></p><p>At the center, you’ll find an Extralight HyperBoost 3 hubset with Boost 110 &amp; 148mm spacing. The six-bolt hubs offer freehubs for Shimano HG/SRAM 8/9/10 or SRAM XD (<a href=\"https://www.extralite.com/Products/HyperBoost3%20R.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Extralite’s website</a> also lists a MicroSpline option for 12s Shimano). Weight for the hubs alone is listed as 74g for the front and 168g for the rear.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5.png\" alt=\"MXC carbon 30mm inner width rim\" width=\"970\" height=\"638\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5.png 970w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5-297x195.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5-800x526.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5-120x79.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130942/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-5-768x505.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px\"></a></p><p>Each wheel is laced with Sapim CX-Super Spoke which is supposedly the lightest aero steel spoke made. The 1.8mm spoke has an aero section that is 0.9mm thick, and 2.0mm wide, with 1.8mm sections at both ends. Each spoke is then held in place with a Sapim black aluminum nipple.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2.jpg\" alt=\"Super light 29&quot; wheelset 30mm inner width\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2.jpg 1440w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-240x300.jpg 240w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-96x120.jpg 96w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-768x960.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/29130921/Radsporttechnik-Mueller-MXCR-Carbon-Extralite-Hyper-3-1060g-carbon-clincher-29-wheelset-super-light-2-1229x1536.jpg 1229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px\"></a></p><p>Add all that together, and you get a tubeless 29er wheelset with a 30mm internal width rim for under 1060g. Pretty impressive. Though it should be for €2,199 (about $2,478)—but that does at least include tubeless tape. There’s also the 90kg (198lb) rider weight limit to consider.</p><p>Need them for your ultra light bike build? Check them out below.</p><p><a href=\"https://radsporttechnik-mueller.de/de/shop/laufradsaetze/29/marathon-xc/mxcr-carbon/laufradsatz-29-mxcr-carbon-boost-extralite-hyper-3-sapim-cx-super-1060g?fbclid=IwAR0TT8bTUaXILj2oBJglPYVJBTrkYXOK8t0dDcMVhRjaMV6sE_w1L6iwQpY\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>radsporttechnik-mueller.de</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"62b330732f7ddb262f77e623f2e2112bdd6976c6a8be11c158ec9fd464cd7b93","category":"Cycling"}